// html is directly connected with browser now using index.html we will connect our java scrpit code to browser
// - <!DOCTYPE html> → Declares the document type as HTML5.
// - <html lang="en"> → Starts the HTML document and specifies the language as English.
// - <head> section → Contains metadata:
// - <meta charset="UTF-8"> → Ensures the page uses UTF-8 encoding (supports most characters).
// - <meta name="viewport" content="width=<device-width>, initial-scale=1.0"> → Makes the page responsive on mobile devices (though width=<device-width> looks like a typo; it should be width=device-width).
// - <title>Document</title> → Sets the page title (shown in the browser tab).
// - <body> section → Contains the visible content of the page.
// - <script src="firstProgram.js"></script> → Loads and executes an external JavaScript file named firstProgram.js --> -->

